<h2>Annual Autumn Rememberance</h2>
<p><strong>October 30 – November 2 at the 5 Points Fountain in Columbia, SC</strong></p>
<p>Beginning in 2006, it creates inspiring personal experiences around the issue of loss grief as well as fostering intimate, social community connections. Based on the Mexican tradition of Day of the Dead, an altar is created for the community to light candles, and bring remembrances to honor the beloved. </p>
<p>Cross-Cultural Community Based Art brings awareness to the value of a more connected, collaborative approach to life. Many other cultural traditions recognize the value of community based rituals and traditions to mark and honor life’s rites of passage – birth, death, etc. </p>
<p>Hundreds of candles have been lit in memory of grandmothers and grandfathers, sisters and brothers, aunts and uncles and children. Mementoes, flowers and photographs grace the altar. People linger to relate their stories of sorrow and a gentle peace fills the air. Some come during lunch hour, through in-between appointments, dressed in Halloween attire, stay long into the night and share stores...young and old, poor and wealthy, Black, White, Hispanic, Oriental, Indian. All walks of life come to remember...together. </p>
